She was nominated for three Tony Awards for her stage work, as well as two Emmy Awards for television work, winning once, for her performance in Eleanor and Franklin (1976).Emmy-Winning Legend Rosemary Murphy Dies at 89, nytimes.com; July 10, 2014; accessed July 10, 2014. She was known for her role in To Kill a Mockingbird (1962).
